• Practice walking carefully and laying it down gently
• Allow child to repeat the sequence multiple times
• Emphasize care and control of movement',
  presentation_steps = '[{"step": 1, "title": "Invitation and Preparation", "description": "Invite the child to work with the mat. Show them how to approach the rolled mat and stand beside it.", "tip": "Use a child-sized mat (approximately 2-3 feet wide and 3-4 feet long) made of durable cotton or polyester."}, {"step": 2, "title": "Picking Up the Mat", "description": "Demonstrate how to pick up the mat with both hands, holding it at roughly hip height, keeping it close to the body.", "tip": "Show the child how to use both hands for balance and stability."}, {"step": 3, "title": "Carrying the Mat", "description": "Walk slowly and carefully while holding the mat, demonstrating controlled movement and awareness of space.", "tip": "Move deliberately and pause frequently to show mindfulness."}, {"step": 4, "title": "Laying Out the Mat", "description": "Show how to gently place the mat on a clear floor space, unrolling it slowly and deliberately.", "tip": "Demonstrate laying it out in a work area away from other children''s work."}, {"step": 5, "title": "Rolling Up the Mat", "description": "Demonstrate the reverse process: rolling the mat up carefully and carrying it back to its storage location.", "tip": "Show how to keep the roll tight and secure while carrying it."}]',
  control_of_error = 'The mat itself provides feedback through its weight and balance. If held improperly, it becomes difficult to carry. The floor space shows if the mat is laid out neatly or crookedly.',
  direct_aims = '["To learn how to carry objects with care and control", "To develop balance and coordination", "To understand sequence and order in classroom activities"]',
  materials = '["Child-sized work mat (approximately 2-3 feet x 3-4 feet)", "Clear floor space for unrolling", "Storage location for the mat"]',
  parent_description = 'Your child is learning to carry and handle materials with care. This foundational skill develops balance, coordination, and respect for classroom materials. It''s one of the first lessons in the Montessori environment and sets the tone for how your child will interact with all future work.',
  why_it_matters = 'Carrying a mat is the bridge between home life and school life. It teaches a child how to move purposefully in a shared environment, how to respect materials, and how to prepare their own workspace. This activity indirectly prepares the child for all future floor work and develops the coordination and awareness needed for success in more complex practical life activities.'
WHERE LOWER(name) = LOWER('Carrying a Mat');

UPDATE montree_classroom_curriculum_works SET
  quick_guide = '• Demonstrate proper grip on the chair (one hand on seat, one on back)
• Show how to lift the chair carefully without noise
• Practice walking with controlled movement
• Demonstrate how to place the chair down gently
• Allow repetition to develop skill and concentration',
  presentation_steps = '[{"step": 1, "title": "Invitation and Initial Observation", "description": "Invite the child to watch you carry a chair. Position yourself beside the chair and explain that we will learn to carry chairs carefully.", "tip": "Use a child-sized chair that is appropriately weighted for the child''s strength."}, {"step": 2, "title": "Demonstrating the Grip", "description": "Show how to place one hand on the seat of the chair and one hand on the back, grasping firmly but gently.", "tip": "The child should be able to grip the chair comfortably without stretching too much."}, {"step": 3, "title": "Lifting the Chair", "description": "Demonstrate how to lift the chair slowly and deliberately, keeping it close to your body and maintaining balance.", "tip": "Emphasize quiet, controlled lifting without jerky movements or noise."}, {"step": 4, "title": "Walking with the Chair", "description": "Walk slowly and deliberately with the chair, showing awareness of space and other people.", "tip": "Move at a pace that allows for complete control and quiet steps."}, {"step": 5, "title": "Placing the Chair Down", "description": "Show how to gently place the chair down without making noise, ensuring it is stable and properly positioned.", "tip": "Demonstrate placing the chair at a table or in a storage location with care."}]',
  control_of_error = 'Noise is immediate feedback. If the child is loud or clumsy, they will hear and feel it. The weight of the chair provides proprioceptive feedback about balance and control.',
  direct_aims = '["To learn to carry furniture with care and control", "To develop awareness of body movement and balance", "To understand how to move quietly in a shared space"]',
  materials = '["Child-sized wooden chair", "Clear pathways in the classroom", "Table or designated storage area for the chair"]',
  parent_description = 'Your child is learning to carry furniture with care and control. This activity develops physical strength, balance, and awareness of movement. It teaches your child to be conscious of their impact on the shared environment and to move with intentionality and respect.',
  why_it_matters = 'Carrying a chair develops essential practical skills for classroom independence. It teaches children how to manage their physical environment, move with control, and be aware of others. These skills are foundational to creating a peaceful, orderly classroom where children can concentrate.'
WHERE LOWER(name) = LOWER('Carrying a Chair');

